%% 3.1.13 Transactions — sequence (layered)
%% Actor > UI > Controller > Service > Repository > Database

sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    actor Actor as Admin or Accountant
    participant UI as UI (/transactions)
    participant TC as Controller (TransactionLogController)
    participant TS as Service (TransactionLogService)
    participant Repo as Repository (IRepository TransactionLog)
    participant DB as Database (SQL Server)

    Actor->>UI: Open Transactions
    Actor->>UI: Set date range From–To, Filter

    UI->>TC: GET /api/TransactionLog/Search?fromDate=&toDate=&keyword=&...
    TC->>TS: SearchAsync(...)
    TS->>Repo: Query logs (append-only reads)
    Repo->>DB: SELECT
    DB-->>Repo: rows
    TS-->>TC: paged ledger
    TC-->>UI: 200 — grid (no edit/delete buttons)

    Actor->>UI: Eye on row — view raw JSON
    UI->>TC: GET /api/TransactionLog/Get/{id}
    TC->>TS: GetByIdAsync(id)
    TS->>Repo: Single log
    Repo->>DB: SELECT
    TS-->>TC: TransactionLogDto
    TC-->>UI: 200 — JSON detail panel

    Note over Actor,DB: BR13 — UI không gọi PUT/DELETE; production nên tắt hoặc chỉ hệ thống nội bộ ghi log (insert-only pipeline).
